Ed,<br><br>
There is no strength in material things. A friend once asked me, when we discussed the relatively little value in material things, &quot;Can a Mercedes love you?&quot; <br><br>
Love is the greatest thing that can be received from another person. <br><br>
While in the bush in Vietnam, I distinctly recall writing in a letter home that as long as I made it home alive, I didn't care what sort of occupation I had, or how much wealth I accumulated. Life is treasure. I have always been grateful for my life being spared.<br><br>
It has been said numerous times on this site that we honor those who fell by living the life granted us, to the fullest. I feel that I am in the midst of accomplishing this. <br><br>
Give up? Give in? Surrender? No way! We have come too far. We have much work to do. Be thankful you are here to do it!<br><br>

